name: link to a link black frame
description:
An international manhunt was initiated by the United States, Canada, and the European Union country to hunt down notorious cybercriminal Lord Bababa for allegedly creating the ultimate Ponzi scheme.


"Ok, this is my ultimate plan. I'm going to sell NFTs which according to twitter.com are just links. Then I'll sell you a link to a link written by me making fun of how fundamentally absurd it is for anyone to pay for a link by creating that link I think. What will this link be? It is a link to something that was created earlier today, a slightly out-of-focus text representation of myself writing creatively at my desk creating something manic that is only to be understood by idiots! I have created something bigger than Ron Howard!"
Meanwhile at the white house


“Lord Babababababa!!” President Joe Biden screamed in a fit of rage. “He will pay, it doesn’t matter how many lives I have to sacrifice to stop him.” He slammed his desk and lit a joint while scratching his butt. “We’re not taking no for an answer!” Everyone will join in our fight against Lord Bababa and his scam!"

—-

The Gallery Gehenna Project is a daily art project where there are multiple frames for each individual artwork, each with different types of rarity applied. Black frames are initially given out for free on hicetnunc. All artworks will be compatible within the Gallery Gehenna Game with each artwork unlocking a playable story segment.
